Definition: characterized by or causing or expressing sadness
Example: growing more melancholy every hour; her melancholic smile; we acquainted him with the melancholy truth
Synonyms: melancholic, noun, person, state, melancholia, characterized, by, or, causing, expressing, sadness, growing, more, every, hour, her, smile, we, acquainted, him, with, the, truth
Category: adj.all
